# === EZmeet — environment (example) ===
# Easiest path: run ./install.sh — it generates this file + all secrets for you.
# Manual path: copy to `.env` and fill in the BOOTSTRAP secrets below. Most
# product config (Google SSO, workspace name, SMTP, AI keys, recording…) is
# configured later in the browser via the first-run /setup wizard — NOT here.
# Never commit the real `.env`.

# ── PostgreSQL ──────────────────────────────────────────────
POSTGRES_DB=eam_meet
POSTGRES_USER=eam_meet
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=change-me
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://eam_meet:change-me@eam-meet-db:5432/eam_meet

# ── Redis ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
REDIS_PASSWORD=change-me
# Optional: set REDIS_URL to use Redis-backed rate limiting (shared across
# instances). Unset → in-process limiter (fine for a single container). Use a
# separate DB (…/1) so it never touches LiveKit's coordination keys.
# REDIS_URL=redis://:change-me@eam-meet-redis:6379/1

# ── NextAuth (generate: openssl rand -hex 32) ───────────────
NEXTAUTH_URL=https://meet.example.com
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=replace-with-openssl-rand-hex-32
AUTH_TRUST_HOST=true

# ── Public URL (used for the /setup link + OAuth redirect URIs) ──
PUBLIC_URL=https://meet.example.com
APP_URL=http://eam-meet:3000

# ── Reverse proxy (Caddy auto-HTTPS — docker-compose.caddy.yml) ──
# Domain Caddy serves + the email for the Let's Encrypt account (optional).
EZMEET_DOMAIN=meet.example.com
EZMEET_TLS_EMAIL=admin@example.com

# ── LiveKit (LIVEKIT_API_SECRET must match livekit.yaml + egress.yaml) ──
LIVEKIT_API_KEY=EAM_MEET_KEY
LIVEKIT_API_SECRET=your-livekit-secret-hex
LIVEKIT_URL=wss://meet.example.com/livekit
LIVEKIT_WS_URL=ws://livekit:7880

# ── Scheduled jobs (reminders / digest / recording retention) ──
CRON_SECRET=replace-with-random

# ── Error tracking (optional — Sentry or self-hosted GlitchTip) ──
# Set to your project's DSN to ship server errors. Unset → structured logs only.
# SENTRY_DSN=https://<publicKey>@<host>/<projectId>

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL — configure these in the /setup wizard or admin panel
# (stored in the database). Uncomment to use env values as a fallback.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Google OAuth — recommended to paste in /setup instead:
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret
# AI / transcription keys — add here or in admin → Settings after setup:
#   DEEPSEEK_API_KEY — powers AI reports, the "Detailed" report & meeting chat
#                      (the core value; set this for a useful install)
#   DEEPGRAM_API_KEY — per-speaker live transcription (OFF by default; opt-in)
# Email (SMTP) drives invites / reminders / the weekly digest — strongly
# recommended. Without any of these the app still boots; features just degrade.
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your-deepseek-key
# DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=your-deepgram-key

# Servers / Remote Access pillar (§15) — native browser RDP. OPT-IN: run
# ./rdp-gateway/setup-keys.sh, start the gateway with `--profile rdp`, and set:
#   RDP_GW_URL=wss://<your-domain>/jet/rdp
#   RDP_GW_PROVISIONER_KEY=...   (PKCS8 PEM private key, newlines as \n — signs tokens)
#   RDP_GW_DELEGATION_PUBKEY=... (SPKI PEM public key, newlines as \n — JWE-wraps creds)
# Absent → the Servers section still works for management; live Connect shows
# "gateway pending" until configured.

# First boot prints a one-time SETUP token to the container logs:
#   docker compose logs eam-meet | grep -A2 SETUP
# Open https://<your-domain>/setup and paste it to begin.
